Two straphangers were bloodied in violent subway incidents in Manhattan on Sunday, cops said. A 34-year-old man was standing on a southbound F subway at the 14th Street-Union Square station around 4:30 p.m. when a stranger struck him in the face, cops said. The victim suffered a cut to the right side of his face and was treated at the scene by emergency workers, police said. The man who struck him took off on foot. It wasnâ€™t clear what preceded the attack or if a weapon was used, cops said. A few hours later, a 28-year-old man was cut on the right hand while walking in a stairwell at the West 4th Street station as he transferred to a D train around 8:30 p.m., according to cops. He refused medical attention on the scene and no further details were available, cops said.